                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_app" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>app</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>appæ</orth></form><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>ядро</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>kernel</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>косточка</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>stone</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>сердцевина</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>core</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>содержание</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>contents</q></tr></sense></sense><etym xml:lang="ru">Из <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/> <w>ḥabb</w> <gloss><q>зерно</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""><w/> <gloss><q>косточка</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/> <w>heb</w> <gloss><q>зерно</q></gloss></mentioned>; отпадение в осетинском начального %iḥ%i, как в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_aʒatxana"/> (тюркское посредство?). Наряду с %iapp%i имеем <ref type="xr" target="#entry_qapp"/> ‘ядро’, ‘testiculum’; если рассматривать %iapp%i и %iqapp%i как два варианта одного и того же слова, то для передачи арабского начального %iḥ%i через %iq%i трудно было бы подыскать еще один пример; не произошла ли в %iqapp%i контаминация с другим %bарабским%b словом <mentioned xml:lang="ar"><lang/> <w>qalb</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>qalb</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>qalp</w> <gloss><q>сердце</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="trk"><w/> <gloss><q>сердцевина</q></gloss></mentioned>, ?</etym><etym xml:lang="en">From <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/> <w>ḥabb</w> <gloss><q>grain</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang=""><w/> <gloss><q>stone</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="ku"><lang/> <w>heb</w> <gloss><q>grain</q></gloss></mentioned>; the fall of the initial %iḥ%i in Ossetic is as in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_aʒatxana"/> (via Turkic?). Alongside with %iapp%i there is <ref type="xr" target="#entry_qapp"/> ‘kernel’, ‘testiculum’; if %iapp%i and %iqapp%i are considered as two variants of the same word, then it would be difficult to find another example on the expression of the initial Arabic %iḥ%i via %iq%i; is not in %iqapp%i a contamination with another %bArabic%b word <mentioned xml:lang="ar"><lang/> <w>qalb</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/> <w>qalb</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/> <w>qalp</w> <gloss><q>heart</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="trk"><w/> <gloss><q>core</q></gloss></mentioned>, ?</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>